what is disgust where does it come from why are some things gross disgust is an emotion that is typically associated with things that are perceived as unclean inedible or infectious in the expression of the emotions in man and animals charles darwin wrote that disgust refers to something revolting primarily in relation to the sense of taste as actually perceived or vividly imagined and secondarily to anything which causes a similar feeling through the sense of smell touch and even of eyesight disgust is one of the basic emotions of robert plutchik's theory of emotions disgust may be further subdivided into physical disgust associated with physical or metaphorical uncleanness and moral disgust a similar feeling related to courses of action Patriotism Empathy Love Consciousness The Descent of Man, and Selection in Relation to Sex Objectivist philosophy Happiness Human Modernism Brain Evolutionism Neuro-linguistic programming Franz Boas Francis Hutcheson (philosopher) Motivation Philosophy of language Facial expression Cyberspace Kashrut Atomism Asperger syndrome David Hume Art Sadism and masochism Philosophy of science Charles Darwin Johann Wolfgang von Goethe Brave New World Sexual orientation Metaphysics Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Religion Homophobia Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Dog Metaphor Sense Aesthetics Darwin from Descent of Man to Emotions Goodness and value theory Olfaction Biology Nationalism Unclean animals __tienne Bonnot de Condillac Friedrich Schleiermacher Dualism (philosophy of mind) Abstraction Friendship George Lakoff Atheism Philosophy of perception Synaesthesia Socrates Touch Nocturnal emission Charles Darwin's views on religion Immanuel Kant The End of Evangelion The Expression of the Emotions in Man and Animals Color Reparative therapy Intelligent design Trademark Conceptual metaphor The Origin of Species Aristotle Taboo food and drink Transsexuality Arthur Schopenhauer Conspiracy theory Myers-Briggs Type Indicator